AI Overview
Interactive data visualization is the graphical representation of data that allows users to engage directly with the visuals to explore and analyze information. This engagement includes actions like clicking, filtering, and zooming, which enable users to actively discover trends, patterns, and insights that might be hidden in static reports. Tools like Tableau, Qlik, and Microsoft Power BI are commonly used to create these dynamic, user-friendly dashboards.
 
Key features and interactions
  • Dynamic exploration:
    Users can interact with the data to change the view, rather than just passively viewing it.
